<item>
            <title>[COMMONSSITE-122] [release-plugin] stage-distributions mojo assumes site directory has basename &apos;site&apos;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/COMMONSSITE-122</link>
                <project id="12310466" key="COMMONSSITE">Apache Commons All</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A multimodule component should have the whole site staged for review, thus from a fully assembled site tree whose default location as produced by&#160;&lt;tt&gt;site:stage&lt;/tt&gt; is &lt;tt&gt;${project.build.directory}/staging&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;. When such a location is set as the &lt;tt&gt;siteDirectory&lt;/tt&gt; configuration property of the specified plugin goal, the site copy fails to find the resulting files because it assumes the &lt;tt&gt;staging&lt;/tt&gt; directory was copied to &lt;tt&gt;site&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
